%N A387261 a(n) is the numerator of the winning probability of the starting player to reach n points first in the game "Risk or Safety", assuming optimal play.
%C A387261 The total number of different strategies is given in A387260. See there for more information.
%e A387261 a(2) = 4: For n=2, the optimal strategy is never to stop, but always try to get two consecutive heads. The winning probability is 1/4*(1 + (3/4)^2 + (3/4)^4 + ...) = 4/7.
